trans-unit.source: Represents the attributes and metadata for an XML Web service method.
This class cannot be inherited.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref> class with the <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> passed in.
A <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> to initialize the properties of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref> common to the <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo>.
The <xref:System.Reflection.MethodBase.IsStatic%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property of the methodInfo parameter is .

-or- The <xref:System.Reflection.MethodBase.GetParameters%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method of the methodInfo parameter does not contain all the parameters required by the method represented by the instance of .
Gets the parameter information for the AsyncCallback parameter of a Begin method in an asynchronous invocation.
A representing the AsyncCallback parameter of a asynchronous method invocation.
Gets the return value of a <xref uid="langword_csharp_Begin" name="Begin" href=""></xref> asynchronous method invocation.
A <xref:System.Reflection.ParameterInfo> representing the <xref:System.IAsyncResult> returned from a <xref uid="langword_csharp_Begin" name="Begin" href=""></xref> asynchronous method invocation.
Gets the parameter information for the AsyncState parameter of a method in an asynchronous invocation.
A representing the AsyncState parameter of a method in an asynchronous invocation.
Begins an asynchronous invocation of the method represented by this <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
The instance of the <xref:System.Object> on which to invoke the method on.
An argument list for the invoked method.
This is an array of objects with the same number, order, and type as the parameters of the method.
If the method does not require any parameters, `values` should be <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
The delegate to call when the asynchronous invoke is complete.
If `callback` is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>, the delegate is not called.
State information that is passed on to the delegate.
An <xref:System.IAsyncResult> which is passed to <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo.EndInvoke*> to obtain the return values from the remote method call.
The target parameteris .
The number, type, and order of parameters in values do not match the signature of the invoked method.
The caller does not have permission to invoke the method.
Gets the attributes and metadata for a <xref uid="langword_csharp_Begin" name="Begin" href=""></xref> method in an asynchronous invocation.
A <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> representing the attributes and metadata for a <xref uid="langword_csharp_Begin" name="Begin" href=""></xref> asynchronous method invocation.

Given an array of <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> that can contain information about both asynchronous and synchronous methods, creates an array of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
An array of <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> representing the asynchronous and synchronous methods for which to create <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref> objects.
An array of , representing the methods within methodInfos.
A asynchronous method is included in methodInfos without a corresponding method.

Given an array of <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo>, where the returned array of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref> can be restricted to only asynchronous or synchronous methods, creates an array of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
An array of <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> representing the asynchronous and synchronous methods for which to create <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref> objects.
A bitwise combination of the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodTypes"></xref> values.
Determines whether just asynchronous or synchronous methods or both are included in the returned array of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
An array of , representing the methods within methodInfos, filtered by the value of types.
A asynchronous method is included in methodInfos without a corresponding method.
Gets the custom attributes applied to the method.
An <xref href="System.Reflection.ICustomAttributeProvider"></xref> representing the custom attributes for the method.
Gets the class that declares the method represented by the current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
The DeclaringType property retrieves a reference to a <xref:System.Type> for the type that declares this member.
A member of a class (or interface) is either declared or inherited from a base class (or interface).

The returned <xref:System.Type> might not be the same as the <xref:System.Type> of the class implementing the XML Web service (if that class derives from a base class and the method represented by this class is declared in that base class then the <xref:System.Type> returned is the base class).
The <xref:System.Type> for the class declaring the method represented by the <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
Ends an asynchronous invocation of the method represented by the current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
The instance of the <xref:System.Object> on which to invoke the method.
The <xref:System.IAsyncResult> returned from <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo.BeginInvoke*>.
An array of objects containing the return value and any by-reference or out parameters of the derived class method.
The target parameter is .

Gets the parameters passed into the method represented by the instance of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
Use an instance of <xref:System.Reflection.ParameterInfo> to obtain information about the parameter's data type, default value, and so on.
InParameters returns an array of <xref:System.Reflection.ParameterInfo> objects representing the parameters passed into a method, in order.

An array of type <xref:System.Reflection.ParameterInfo> containing the parameters passed into the method represented by the instance of <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.
Invokes the method represented by the current <xref href="System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo"></xref>.

An argument list for the invoked method.
This is an array of objects with the same number, order, and type as the parameters of the method.

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the method is invoked asynchronously; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.

if the methodInfo parameter is a method of an asynchronous invocation; otherwise, .

<xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the return type is void; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
Gets the attributes and metadata for a synchronous method.
A <xref:System.Reflection.MethodInfo> representing the attributes and metadata for a method.

If <xref:System.Web.Services.Protocols.LogicalMethodInfo.IsAsync*> is <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>, then the value of this property is <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
